sentences: Robbie Montgomery (born June 16, 1940) is an American soul singer and restaurateur.
She is noted for being one of the original Ikettes in the Ike & Tina Turner Revue in the 1960s.
In the 1970s, Montgomery was a backing vocalist for acts such as Stevie Wonder, Barbra Streisand, the Rolling Stones, and Joe Cocker.
Robbie Marie Montgomery was born on June 16, 1940, in Columbus, Mississippi, to Ora Gray and James Montgomery.

Welcome to Sweetie Pies, a reality show which focused on Montgomery running her soul food restaurants, premiered on the Oprah Winfrey Network on October 15, 2011.

In January 2020, Sweetie Pie's opened a new location in Jackson, Mississippi.
In the 1980s, Mayor Vincent Schoemehl appointed the St. Louis Kings of Rhythm, which included Montgomery, ambassadors for the City of St. Louis.
In 2010, George Lombardi, the director of the Missouri Department of Corrections, presented Montgomery with a plaque honoring her for her willingness to help ex-offenders.
Welcome to Sweetie Pie's won the NAACP Image Award for Best Reality Series in 2013 and 2016.
